SOLID is Applied
✅ S — Single Responsibility
ViewModel → UI logic
UseCase → business logic
Repository → data operations
ApiService → networking

👉 Each class has one job.

✅ O — Open/Closed
Add new data sources (Cache, GraphQL) without modifying existing repository interface.
👉 Use abstractions so you can extend behavior without modifying existing code.

✅ L — Liskov Substitution
UserRepositoryImpl can replace UserRepository anywhere without breaking behavior.
✅ I — Interface Segregation
Separate interfaces for different features (e.g., AuthRepository, UserRepository)
✅ D — Dependency Inversion
High-level modules depend on abstractions (UserRepository)
Implementations injected using Hilt


